Author: Konstantin <rsboarder@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 16 22:15:17 2026 +0400

    Replace term-overlap heuristic with LLM agreement judge
    
    Auto-deliberation now uses Cursor CLI + gemini-2.5-flash to judge whether
    R1 responses agree. The judge scores 1-5 (disagree→consensus) with a
    reason. Costs ~$0.001 per call, takes ~1-2s.
    
    Falls back to term-overlap heuristic if Cursor CLI is unavailable.
    
    New module: owlex/agreement.py
    - score_agreement(): sends truncated R1 responses to gemini-2.5-flash
    - Anonymous labels (Response A/B/C) for unbiased judging
    - Robust JSON parsing with regex fallback
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

